notes.text: Multicluster Engine for Kubernetes 2.5.2 General Availability release images, which fix bugs and update container images.
notes.title: Topic

notes.text:
Multicluster engine for Kubernetes v2.5.2 images

Multicluster engine for Kubernetes provides the foundational components
that are necessary for the centralized management of multiple
Kubernetes-based clusters across data centers, public clouds, and private
clouds.

You can use the engine to create new Red Hat OpenShift Container Platform
clusters or to bring existing Kubernetes-based clusters under management by
importing them. After the clusters are managed, you can use the APIs that
are provided by the engine to distribute configuration based on placement
policy.

cwe.name: Exposure of Sensitive Information to an Unauthorized Actor

notes.text: An information exposure flaw was found in the sanitize-html package, when used on the backend with the style attribute allowed. This issue may allow an attacker to enumerate files in the system, including project dependencies, to gather details about the file system structure and dependencies of the targeted server.

notes.text: Jose was found to have an uncontrolled resource consumption vulnerability. Under certain conditions, the user's environment can consume an unreasonable amount of CPU time or memory during JWE decryption operations, leading to a denial of service.
